9
What You’ll Build / Lead / Own:
Design and own the post-download growth funnel across LXME Pay and LXME Invest.
Drive activation, repeat transactions, and retention through data-led interventions.
Optimize distribution business conversions to maximize accounts & AUM .
Lead partner-led growth initiatives such as bootcamps and collaborations.
Build and manage growth dashboards, cohorts, and analytics frameworks.
Experiment with journeys, communications, and in-app behavior to increase revenue per user.
Work cross-functionally with Product, Marketing, Data, and Sales to align user experience with business outcomes.
What Success Looks Like:
Increase Conversion rate from activation → revenue.
Growth in monthly growth in AUM and TPV.
Increase Retention & reactivation rates.
Reduce CAC through improved funnel efficiency.
Improve Revenue per active user (RPU).
Consistent data-driven experimentation and insight generation.
Who You Are:
A growth operator who thrives at the intersection of product, data, and user psychology.
Obsessed with cohorts, funnels, and retention metrics.
Analytical, execution-focused, and relentless about driving business outcomes.
Experienced in fintech or payments and comfortable scaling 0→1→10 growth journeys.
Passionate about LXME’s mission to make financial confidence accessible to every woman.
Qualifications & Experience:
4–6 years of experience in fintech / payments / consumer tech growth or product roles.
Deep understanding of user lifecycle metrics, funnel analytics, and growth frameworks.
Hands-on with data tools (Appsflyer, Mixpanel, Moengage, SQL, GA4, or equivalent).
Proven track record of driving measurable revenue or user retention outcomes.
Exposure to mutual funds, UPI, or financial platforms preferred.
